Package: hexcalc
Version: 1.0.0-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Izai Alejandro Zalles Merino <izai.zalles@example.com>
Installed-Size: 41
Depends: python3 (>= 3.6)
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/izaizalles/hexcalc
Description: Professional hexadecimal calculator CLI tool
 HexCalc is a powerful command-line tool for performing hexadecimal
 arithmetic and bitwise operations. It supports multiple operands
 and various output formats.
 .
 Features:
  * Arithmetic operations (add, subtract, multiply, divide, modulo, power)
  * Bitwise operations (AND, OR, XOR, NOT, shifts)
  * Multiple operands support
  * Output formats: hexadecimal, decimal, binary, octal
  * Verbose mode for detailed operation information
  * Professional CLI interface similar to sqlmap
 .
 This tool is useful for penetration testing, reverse engineering,
 network engineering, and general development tasks.
